{
  "stem": "3820.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we stayed there for a while.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But then my father, my dad, decided that it might be easier for us if we went out of the DP camp to have papers, try to get papers through HIAS and his brothers in America to come to America.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we moved to Stuttgart.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we lived in Stuttgart in part of 1946 into 1947 when we received our papers to go to the United States.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We came to the United States April 1, 1947.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had a harrowing journey.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We boarded ship in-- first of all, they isolated us for a period of time, maybe as long as two months because of all the shots and things.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They wanted to be sure that no one was ill.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we boarded a, a ship on March 10, I think it was or somewhere around there called the SS Ernie Pyle.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was a troop ship.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But a short time out into the ocean, they had some trouble.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they had to turn back.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we went-- we went back to-- we were-- they stayed outside the English waters in England.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So we had to wait for another ship to take that ship's refugees to the United States and come back for us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So we, we crossed over a plank of water from one ship to the other.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The ship that brought us to the United States was the SS Marilyn Marie.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we arrived in, in New York April 1, 1947.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my father had an uncle here from the early years before World War II-- before WWI, I think.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he had been ill, so he wasn't at the dock to meet us.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
